===Noun===
'''incunabulum''', ('''incunabula''')
# A book, single sheet, or image that was printed — not handwritten — before the year 1501 in Europe.
#: ''The British Library’s collection of incunabula (15th century printing) is unrivalled in size and scope: some 12,500 incunabula representing about 10,390 editions, out of an estimated surviving 28,000 editions.''
